  <refnamediv>
    <refname>&dhpackage;</refname>

    <refpurpose>Modem Lights applet for the GNOME panel.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>&dhpackage;</command>

	<arg><option>--activate-goad-server </option><replaceable>[=GOAD_ID]</replaceable></arg>
    
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>

    <para><command>&dhpackage;</command> This applet can be used to tell if
      your modem is working, and to track its behavior and performance. It
      can also be configured to call a separate script or program to have
      your modem connect and disconnect when you click on the button with
      the single green light.</para>

    <para>To add this applet to a Panel, right-click on the Panel and
      choose Applets->Network->Modem Lights</para>

  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>OPTIONS</title>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>--activate-goad-server</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>(Internal use only) GOAD server ID to activate.</para>
          <para>GOAD_ID is usually the applet name [<command>&dhpackage;</command>]</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>AUTHOR</title>

    <para>This manual page was written by &dhusername; &dhemail; for
      the &debian; system (but may be used by others).</para>

  </refsect1>
